@startuml class_error_logger
title ErrorLogger Class Diagram

package "src.error_logger" {
    class ErrorLogger {
        - _logger: logging.Logger
        + __init__(log_file: str = "error.log"): None
        + log_unsupported_operation(operation_name: str): None
        + log_invalid_operand(operand: str, reason: str): None
        + log_incorrect_arity(operation_name: str, expected: int, got: int): None
        + log_division_by_zero(numerator: float): None
        + log_invalid_domain(operation_name: str, operand: float, reason: str): None
    }
}

package "python.logging" {
    class Logger {
        + setLevel(level): void
        + addHandler(handler): void
        + error(msg, *args): void
    }
    class FileHandler
    class Formatter
}

package "main" {
    class main_module {
        + main(): void
    }
}

package "src.cli" {
    class cli_module {
        + interactive_session(calculator): void
    }
}

ErrorLogger --> Logger: uses
Logger --> FileHandler: adds
FileHandler --> Formatter: uses

main_module --> ErrorLogger: instantiates
cli_module --> ErrorLogger: instantiates

note right of ErrorLogger
  Unique logger per instance (id-keyed).
  propagate = False — no console output.
  FileHandler in append mode, UTF-8.
end note

@enduml
